Getting started with Devops 101
===============================
Week 1:
-------
Steps taken:
------------
Fresh install of Ubuntu Desktop.
Sign-up for a Gmail account [to use for anything related sites sign-ups].
Sign-up for a GitHub account.

Generate an SSH key-pair for GitHub account.
-- ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -f ~/.ssh/gitREPO -C "DESK1"

Copy the SSH public-key to GitHub for pull/push authentication.
-- less ~/.ssh/gitREPO.pub
-- Click on Proilfe Icon -> Settings -> SSH and GPG keys -> New SSH key
-- -> Title -> Key [You paste the .pub] -> Add SSH key.

Create a git repository.

Install and configure git.
-- sudo apt install git -y
-- git config --global user.name "Your Name"
-- git config --global user.email "youremail@example.com"

Create a local git repository, add files, commit and check history [log].
-- mkdir -p Devops && cd Devops
-- git init
-- echo "Hey, strangers!" > README.md
-- git add .
-- git commit -m "First commit."
-- git branch -M main
-- git remote add origin git@github.com:eKROWN/eKROWN-GPT.git
-- **git log
-- **git checkout -b feature-branch
-- **git status
-- **git log --follow README.md
-- **git show

Create a .gitignore file to add files/directories not to be push into GitHub repo.
-- nano .gitignore
-- nano Workkthrough.eKRN [this file is added into .gitignore as /Workthrough.eKRN]
-- using '/' before the filename prevent the file from showing up in GitHub repository.
